    "body": "Please do shorten the first (title line) of the commit message. It shows up like this now:\r\n```\r\n* 76660fcb0992034bb15b00d5bfb8b498cc9673ee Per #11862. Most bitcoin.conf options apply to all three networks, however some apply only to mainnet unless specified in a section. As stands, conf file has no indication that sections are now in use or are in some circumstances mandatory (eg, changing rpcport for testnet.) (Alistair Mann) (pull/15387/head)\r\n```\r\nThe format of a commit message is supposed to be\r\n```\r\n<short title>\r\n<empty line>\r\n<description ...> (may be multiple lines)\r\n```",
